Rating: 4
YUM! This gets a 4 for ease & speed. I had some fresh rosemary so I used that instead. No problem to get to the syrupy stage -- I deglazed with the wine then added a little broth. I think I cooked it a little longer than prescribed. We had pasta but it would be great with mashed potatoes.

Rating: 3
I used beef broth instead of chicken this time...much richer. Also, I deglazed the pan with about one quarter cup of the broth. Once it was all but evaporated, I added the wine and additional tarragon. Much closer to a "syrupy" consistency.

Rating: 3
This is a short ingredient recipe and easy to make. Absolutely declicious. However, I have prepared this dish twice and have not been able to get to a syrupy stage. I've thickend it with a slurry made of flour and the liquid from the sauce. Worked well. I doubled the recipe for company and doubled the lemon juice, big mistake. Served this with couscous and vegetable medley. Was liked by all.

